Starting Monday morning until Friday, buses and taxis will be permitted to operate from 5am to 8pm. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Transport has relaxed public transport operating hours to accommodate some SASSA grant beneficiaries. Starting Monday morning until Friday, buses and taxis will be permitted to operate from 5am to 8pm. WATCH: Taxi industry announces plans to curb COVID-19 During the 21-day lockdown, taxis and e-hailing services are allowed to operate only between 5am and 9am and 4pm and 8pm, to transport workers in essential services.